Fox News Channel (FNC) will launch an over-the-top opinion platform titled Fox Nation. The standalone opinion streaming service is expected to debut in Q4 2018, with a price to be announced at a later date. Designed to enhance the Fox News viewer experience, Fox Nation will “take a deep dive into the big issues of the day, with live exclusive daily streaming content and long-form programming”. Fox Nation will also include access to exclusive events and over 20 years of archival FNC programming. Interaction with FNC’s opinion hosts and personalities will also be a mainstay of the new platform. Fox Nation will be housed at Fox News headquarters in New York.